@startuml Cloudflare SpeedTest SDK Integration
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam ParticipantPadding 20
skinparam BoxPadding 10

title Cloudflare SpeedTest SDK - API Usage Sequence\nVue.js Application Integration Pattern

actor User
participant "SpeedTestControls" as Controls <<Vue Component>>
participant "App.vue" as App <<Root Component>>
participant "Vue Reactivity" as Vue <<System>>
participant "SpeedTest SDK" as SDK <<@cloudflare/speedtest>>
participant "Cloudflare Edge" as Edge <<Network>>
collections "UI Components" as UI <<Speedometers, Scores>>

== Initialization ==

User -> Controls: Click "Start Test"
activate Controls
Controls -> App: emit('start-test')
deactivate Controls
activate App

App -> App: Reset previous results
note right
  results.value = {
    download: null,
    upload: null,
    latency: null,
    ...
  }
  scores.value = null
  summary.value = null
end note

App -> SDK: new SpeedTest(config)
note right
  markRaw(new SpeedTest({
    autoStart: false,
    measurements: [...]
  }))

  ⚠️ markRaw() prevents
  Vue reactivity issues
  with private fields
end note
activate SDK
SDK --> App: speedTest instance
deactivate SDK

== Event Handler Registration ==

App -> SDK: speedTest.onRunningChange = callback
note right
  (running) => {
    isRunning.value = running
    if (running) {
      setTimeout(() => {
        showOverlay.value = true
      }, 500)
    }
  }
end note

App -> SDK: speedTest.onResultsChange = callback
note right
  ({ type }) => {
    const res = speedTest.results
    const download = res.getDownloadBandwidth()
    if (download !== null) {
      results.value.download = download
    }
    // ... update all metrics
  }
end note

App -> SDK: speedTest.onFinish = callback
note right
  (testResults) => {
    summary.value = testResults.getSummary()
    scores.value = testResults.getScores()
  }
end note

== Test Execution ==

App -> SDK: speedTest.play()
activate SDK

SDK -> App: onRunningChange(true)
activate App
App -> Vue: isRunning.value = true
activate Vue
Vue -> UI: Re-render components
activate UI
UI --> User: Show "Testing..." state\nEnable Stop button
deactivate UI
deactivate Vue

App -> App: setTimeout(2000ms)
note right
  ✅ FIXED: Delay increased from 500ms to 2000ms
  Downloads start at ~1s
  Overlay appears at 2s
  User sees drum speedometer rolling first
end note
App -> Vue: showOverlay.value = true
Vue -> UI: Show UltimateQuestionOverlay
UI --> User: Easter egg appears\n"Answer: 42?"
deactivate App

== Measurement 1: Initial Latency Check ==

SDK -> Edge: Send 1 ping packet
activate Edge
note right SDK
  { type: 'latency', numPackets: 1 }
  Duration: ~1 second
end note
Edge --> SDK: Latency response (15ms)
deactivate Edge

SDK -> App: onResultsChange({ type: 'latency' })
activate App
App -> SDK: speedTest.results.getUnloadedLatency()
SDK --> App: 15.3 (ms)
App -> Vue: results.value.latency = 15.3
activate Vue
Vue -> UI: Update latency display
UI --> User: "15.3 ms" shown
deactivate UI
deactivate Vue
deactivate App

== Measurement 2: Download Warmup ==

SDK -> Edge: Download 8 × 100 KB chunks
activate Edge
note right SDK
  { type: 'download', bytes: 1e5, count: 8 }
  Total: 800 KB
  Duration: ~2 seconds
end note
Edge --> SDK: Data chunks + timing
deactivate Edge

SDK -> App: onResultsChange({ type: 'download' })
activate App
App -> SDK: speedTest.results.getDownloadBandwidth()
SDK --> App: 45000000 (45 Mbps in bps)
App -> Vue: results.value.download = 45000000
activate Vue
Vue -> UI: Update drum speedometer
note right UI
  Convert bps to Mbps:
  45000000 / 1e6 = 45 Mbps

  Drum position:
  (45 * 60px) - baseOffset
end note
UI --> User: Speedometer shows 45 Mbps\n(drum rotates up)
deactivate UI
deactivate Vue
deactivate App

== Measurement 3: Extended Latency Baseline ==

SDK -> Edge: Send 20 ping packets
activate Edge
note right SDK
  { type: 'latency', numPackets: 20 }
  Statistical accuracy
  Duration: ~2 seconds
end note
Edge --> SDK: 20 latency measurements
deactivate Edge

SDK -> App: onResultsChange({ type: 'latency' })
activate App
App -> SDK: speedTest.results.getUnloadedLatency()
SDK --> App: 16.1 (ms) [averaged]
App -> SDK: speedTest.results.getUnloadedJitter()
SDK --> App: 2.3 (ms)
App -> Vue: results.value.latency = 16.1\nresults.value.jitter = 2.3
activate Vue
Vue -> UI: Update latency & jitter displays
UI --> User: Updated LED displays
deactivate UI
deactivate Vue
deactivate App

== Measurements 4-6: Progressive Downloads ==

loop Download Tests (100KB, 1MB, 10MB)
  SDK -> Edge: Download progressively larger chunks
  activate Edge
  note right SDK
    Measurements:
    - { type: 'download', bytes: 1e5, count: 6 }  (600 KB)
    - { type: 'download', bytes: 1e6, count: 6 }  (6 MB)
    - { type: 'download', bytes: 1e7, count: 4 }  (40 MB)

    Purpose: Establish sustained throughput
    Duration: ~15 seconds total
  end note
  Edge --> SDK: Data + timing + loaded latency
  deactivate Edge

  SDK -> App: onResultsChange({ type: 'download' })
  activate App
  App -> SDK: speedTest.results.getDownloadBandwidth()
  SDK --> App: Increasing speeds (48, 50, 52 Mbps)
  App -> SDK: speedTest.results.getDownLoadedLatency()
  note right SDK: ⚠️ Note typo: DownLoaded (capital L)
  SDK --> App: 18.7 (ms)
  App -> SDK: speedTest.results.getDownLoadedJitter()
  SDK --> App: 4.2 (ms)
  App -> Vue: Update all download metrics
  activate Vue
  Vue -> UI: Real-time speedometer updates
  UI --> User: Drum scrolls to higher speeds\n50 → 52 Mbps
  deactivate UI
  deactivate Vue
  deactivate App
end

== Measurement 7: Upload Warmup ==

SDK -> Edge: Upload 8 × 100 KB chunks
activate Edge
note right SDK
  { type: 'upload', bytes: 1e5, count: 8 }
  Total: 800 KB
  Duration: ~5 seconds
end note
Edge --> SDK: Upload timing data
deactivate Edge

SDK -> App: onResultsChange({ type: 'upload' })
activate App
App -> SDK: speedTest.results.getUploadBandwidth()
SDK --> App: 8000000 (8 Mbps in bps)
App -> Vue: results.value.upload = 8000000
activate Vue
Vue -> UI: Update upload speedometer
UI --> User: Upload drum shows 8 Mbps
deactivate UI
deactivate Vue
deactivate App

== Measurement 8: Packet Loss Test ==

SDK -> Edge: Send 1000 packets (100 batches × 10)
activate Edge
note right SDK
  { type: 'packetLoss', numPackets: 1e3, batchSize: 10 }

  TURN server-based
  ⚠️ May deprecate in future
  Duration: ~10 seconds
end note
Edge --> SDK: Packet receipt confirmations
deactivate Edge

SDK -> App: onResultsChange({ type: 'packetLoss' })
activate App
App -> SDK: speedTest.results.getPacketLoss()
SDK --> App: 0.01 (1% loss)
App -> Vue: results.value.packetLoss = 0.01
activate Vue
Vue -> UI: Update packet loss display
note right UI
  Convert to percentage:
  0.01 × 100 = 1.0%
end note
UI --> User: "1.0%" packet loss shown
deactivate UI
deactivate Vue
deactivate App

== Measurements 9-10: Large Uploads ==

loop Upload Tests (1MB, 10MB)
  SDK -> Edge: Upload progressively larger chunks
  activate Edge
  note right SDK
    Measurements:
    - { type: 'upload', bytes: 1e6, count: 6 }  (6 MB)
    - { type: 'upload', bytes: 1e7, count: 4 }  (40 MB)

    Duration: ~15 seconds total
  end note
  Edge --> SDK: Upload timing + loaded latency
  deactivate Edge

  SDK -> App: onResultsChange({ type: 'upload' })
  activate App
  App -> SDK: speedTest.results.getUploadBandwidth()
  SDK --> App: Increasing speeds (9, 10 Mbps)
  App -> SDK: speedTest.results.getUpLoadedLatency()
  SDK --> App: 22.1 (ms)
  App -> SDK: speedTest.results.getUpLoadedJitter()
  SDK --> App: 3.8 (ms)
  App -> Vue: Update all upload metrics
  activate Vue
  Vue -> UI: Real-time updates
  UI --> User: Upload speeds stabilize at 10 Mbps
  deactivate UI
  deactivate Vue
  deactivate App
end

== Measurement 11: Final Large Download ==

SDK -> Edge: Download 4 × 25 MB chunks
activate Edge
note right SDK
  { type: 'download', bytes: 2.5e7, count: 4 }
  Total: 100 MB
  Final sustained throughput test
  Duration: ~10 seconds
end note
Edge --> SDK: Final download data + timing
deactivate Edge

SDK -> App: onResultsChange({ type: 'download' })
activate App
App -> SDK: speedTest.results.getDownloadBandwidth()
SDK --> App: 53000000 (53 Mbps) [final]
App -> Vue: results.value.download = 53000000
activate Vue
Vue -> UI: Final speedometer update
UI --> User: Download speed peaks at 53 Mbps
deactivate UI
deactivate Vue
deactivate App

== Test Completion ==

SDK -> SDK: Calculate summary statistics\nCalculate quality scores
note right SDK
  Summary aggregates all measurements

  Scores calculated:
  - Streaming: download + latency + packet loss
  - Gaming: latency + jitter + packet loss
  - RTC: up/down + latency + jitter
end note

SDK -> App: onFinish(testResults)
activate App

App -> SDK: testResults.getSummary()
SDK --> App: Summary object
note right App
  {
    download: 53000000,
    upload: 10000000,
    latency: 16.1,
    jitter: 2.3,
    downloadLatency: 18.7,
    downloadJitter: 4.2,
    uploadLatency: 22.1,
    uploadJitter: 3.8,
    packetLoss: 0.01
  }
end note

App -> SDK: testResults.getScores()
SDK --> App: Scores object
note right App
  {
    streaming: {
      points: 85,
      classification: 'good'
    },
    gaming: {
      points: 72,
      classification: 'average'
    },
    rtc: {
      points: 91,
      classification: 'great'
    }
  }
end note

App -> Vue: summary.value = summary\nscores.value = scores
activate Vue
Vue -> UI: Render QualityScores component\nRender SummaryDetails component
activate UI
UI --> User: Show quality badges:\n✓ Streaming: Good (85)\n✓ Gaming: Average (72)\n✓ RTC: Great (91)
deactivate UI
deactivate Vue

deactivate App

SDK -> App: onRunningChange(false)
activate App
App -> Vue: isRunning.value = false
activate Vue
Vue -> UI: Re-render controls
activate UI
UI --> User: "Start Test" button enabled\nStatus: "Test completed"
deactivate UI
deactivate Vue
deactivate App

deactivate SDK

== User Interaction (Optional) ==

User -> UI: Answer "42" in overlay
activate UI
UI -> App: emit('correct-answer')
deactivate UI
activate App
App -> Vue: showOverlay.value = false
activate Vue
Vue -> UI: Hide overlay, restore opacity
UI --> User: Test results fully visible
deactivate UI
deactivate Vue
deactivate App

note over User, Edge
  Total test duration: ~30-60 seconds
  Total bandwidth consumed: ~200 MB
  Network requests: ~50-100 to Cloudflare edge

  Key API patterns demonstrated:
  ✓ markRaw() wrapper for Vue compatibility
  ✓ Event-driven architecture (3 callbacks)
  ✓ Real-time progressive updates
  ✓ Null checking before using results
  ✓ Unit conversion (bps → Mbps, decimal → %)
end note

@enduml
